{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":5000,"text":"[SHIT]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":7000,"text":"This is arguably the back end\nof the design of animals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13000,"text":"But the reason\nI put this up here is because"},{"time":16444,"text":"when I was in Africa last year,\nmy wife and I were driving around,"},{"time":20579,"text":"we had this wonderful guide,"},{"time":22825,"text":"who showed us something\nthat surprised both of us,"},{"time":26000,"text":"and it was very revealing\nin terms of the fascination"},{"time":29000,"text":"that comes with the design of animals."},{"time":31000,"text":"It turns out that in about the 1880s,\nthe missionaries came to Africa"},{"time":35000,"text":"to spread the word of Christianity,"},{"time":37000,"text":"to teach English to the natives."},{"time":39001,"text":"And they brought blackboards and chalk."},{"time":41918,"text":"And I'd like you to imagine\nthat that's a blackboard,"},{"time":44495,"text":"and I just used some chalk on there."},{"time":46341,"text":"And they brought\nquite a bit of this stuff."},{"time":48845,"text":"But over the years,\nthe blackboards were fine,"},{"time":51427,"text":"but they ran out of chalk."},{"time":53428,"text":"And this is a real crisis for them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55591,"text":"And that's where the hyena comes in."},{"time":58718,"text":"The hyena is probably\nthe most perfectly designed"},{"time":61100,"text":"scavenging animal in the world."},{"time":63001,"text":"It strip-mines carcasses,\nand it has amazing teeth,"},{"time":67000,"text":"because it enables the hyena\nto essentially eat bones."},{"time":72000,"text":"Now, the end product of that action\nis up on the board here."},{"time":77751,"text":"What the missionaries would do is,\nthey'd walk around"},{"time":83037,"text":"and they'd pick up hyena shit."},{"time":85000,"text":"And the incredible thing\nabout hyena shit is, it makes great chalk."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88959,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":90079,"text":"That's not what I'm here to talk about,"},{"time":92000,"text":"but it is a fascinating aspect\nof animal design."},{"time":96635,"text":"What I'm here to talk about is the camel."},{"time":99000,"text":"When I started talking to Richard"},{"time":101000,"text":"about what I was going to speak about,"},{"time":103000,"text":"I had recently come back from Jordan,"},{"time":105648,"text":"where I had an amazing\nexperience with a camel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":112000,"text":"And we were in the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":113445,"text":"Richard Wurman: That's the end!\nKeith Bellows: Yeah, yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116286,"text":"We were in the desert,\nin Wadi Rum, in a small Jeep."},{"time":119555,"text":"There were four of us,\ntwo Bedouin drivers."},{"time":122000,"text":"You can just imagine,\nthis expanse is an ocean of sand,"},{"time":126000,"text":"105 degrees, one water bottle."},{"time":128698,"text":"And we were driving in what they told us\nwas their very, very best Jeep."},{"time":134182,"text":"Didn't look like it to me."},{"time":136626,"text":"And as we started to go\nthrough the desert,"},{"time":140695,"text":"the Jeep broke down."},{"time":142000,"text":"The guys got out, they put the hood up,"},{"time":144000,"text":"they started working\nunder the hood, got it going again."},{"time":146699,"text":"About a hundred yards, it broke down."},{"time":148493,"text":"This went on about 6-7 times,\nwe were getting more and more alarmed,"},{"time":151794,"text":"we were also getting deeper\nand deeper into the desert."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154476,"text":"And eventually,\nour worst nightmare happened:"},{"time":157000,"text":"they flooded the engine."},{"time":159000,"text":"And they said, \"Ah, no problem!\nWe just get out and walk.\""},{"time":163195,"text":"And we said, \"We get out and walk?\""},{"time":165001,"text":"One water bottle, remember,\nguys, four people."},{"time":167277,"text":"And they said, \"Yeah, yeah, we'll walk.\nWe'll find some camels.\""},{"time":170944,"text":"We got out and walked, and sure enough,"},{"time":172921,"text":"about half a mile, we came\nover the crest of this hill,"},{"time":175555,"text":"and there was a huge gathering\nof Bedouin with their camels."},{"time":178477,"text":"The guy went up and started dickering,"},{"time":180396,"text":"and 10 dollars later, we had four camels."},{"time":183000,"text":"They went down like elevators;\nwe got on them."},{"time":185542,"text":"They went back up, and the Bedouin,\neach Bedouin, four of them,"},{"time":189000,"text":"got behind each of the camels\nwith a little whip."},{"time":192000,"text":"And they started slashing away\nat the back of the camels,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and they started galloping."},{"time":196316,"text":"And if you've ever been on a camel,\nit is a very, very uncomfortable ride."},{"time":200000,"text":"There's also one other aspect\nabout these camels."},{"time":203000,"text":"About every 10 steps, they lean back"},{"time":205000,"text":"and try to take a chunk out of your leg."}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":208103,"text":"So we kept on going,"},{"time":210000,"text":"and this camel kept on trying\nto take a chunk out of my leg."},{"time":213000,"text":"And eventually, three miles later,\nwe arrived at our destination,"},{"time":216158,"text":"where a Jeep was supposed to meet us."},{"time":218000,"text":"And the camels come down\nagain like elevators,"},{"time":220476,"text":"we sort of clumsily get off,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and they, obviously, try to take\nanother chunk out of my leg."},{"time":225000,"text":"And I've developed\na very wonderful relationship"},{"time":228000,"text":"with this creature by this point,"},{"time":230000,"text":"and I've realized\nthat this is a mean son of a bitch."},{"time":234000,"text":"And much meaner, by the way,\nthan the Bedouin who greeted me"},{"time":237000,"text":"and tried to sell me\none of his 26 daughters"},{"time":239564,"text":"to take back to the States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242000,"text":"So as we talked, Richard and I,"},{"time":243898,"text":"I said, \"You know, maybe\nI should bring a camel."},{"time":246183,"text":"It's the best designed\nanimal in the world.\""},{"time":248440,"text":"He went, \"Nah. I don't think\nwe want to be bringing a camel.\""},{"time":251348,"text":"And you should be really glad\nwe decided not to bring the camel."},{"time":254509,"text":"So I did the next best thing."},{"time":257000,"text":"I went to the Washington Zoo."},{"time":258985,"text":"Richard said, \"I want you to get up\nclose and personal with this camel."},{"time":263569,"text":"I want you to inspect its mouth,\nlook at its teeth."},{"time":266537,"text":"Go underneath it.\nGo above it. Go around it."},{"time":269000,"text":"Pull its tail up; take a look in there."},{"time":271738,"text":"I want you to get as close\nto that camel as you possibly can.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":275000,"text":"So, I got a National Geographic film crew."},{"time":278666,"text":"We went down there,\nand I took one look at this camel."},{"time":284382,"text":"It is a 2,000 pound creature\nwho is in rut."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":291818,"text":"Now, if you've ever seen\na 2,000 pound camel in rut,"},{"time":294699,"text":"it is a scary, scary thing to behold."},{"time":297857,"text":"And if Richard thought I was getting\nin the ring with that camel,"},{"time":301547,"text":"someone was smoking Bedouin high grade."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":305206,"text":"So we got as close to it as possible,"},{"time":309000,"text":"and I'm going to share this."},{"time":310366,"text":"Chris, if you want to roll this film."},{"time":312159,"text":"Then I'm going to show you"},{"time":313437,"text":"a little bit more\nabout the design of camels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":315557,"text":"Do you want to roll the film?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":317287,"text":"(Adventure music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352205,"text":"(Video) Hello. This is Keith Bellows"},{"time":353965,"text":"with the TED National Geographic\nCamel Investigation Unit."},{"time":357483,"text":"I'm here to look\nat the ultimate desert machine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360916,"text":"(Music continues)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367912,"text":"Keith Bellows: And you'll note\nI started chewing gum"},{"time":370429,"text":"because I was around this camel all day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":372964,"text":"(Video) That's it, OK. No!"},{"time":375627,"text":"See, now he's getting\na little overexcited."},{"time":377681,"text":"So we'll need to be very careful\naround him. Don't let him get you."},{"time":403174,"text":"Now, you can see copious amounts\nof saliva in there."},{"time":410276,"text":"I always called myself\nthe unstable stable boy."},{"time":413424,"text":"Their nose, you can see\nhis nose is flared right now."},{"time":417285,"text":"When they're in rut,\nthey're similar to seals"},{"time":420771,"text":"in the way, like, a seal has\nto open its nose to breathe."},{"time":425000,"text":"And they're similar.\nThey have to consciously open their nose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":428987,"text":"KB: Ears?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":430012,"text":"SK: They are small.\nBut they have excellent hearing."},{"time":434000,"text":"But not big; for instance,\nin zebras, they have a huge ear"},{"time":440095,"text":"that's very mobile, so they can\nactually turn them both around."},{"time":444000,"text":"And they use them in the same way\nwe use our binocular vision."},{"time":447000,"text":"They use that to pinpoint sound."},{"time":450000,"text":"The desert's extremely windy\nas well as being very cold."},{"time":454181,"text":"So not only do they have\nthe very long eyelashes,"},{"time":458676,"text":"but there's the secondary --"},{"time":460559,"text":"I guess you'd call it\nthe [unclear] or whatever."},{"time":464000,"text":"It's this hair that's above the eyes,\nand below it, it's longer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"Most people think\nthat the humps store water."},{"time":472000,"text":"They don't. They store fat."},{"time":477000,"text":"Now, I'm not a chemist,\nbut basically what happens"},{"time":481603,"text":"is the fat is oxidized by their breathing."},{"time":487491,"text":"And that will turn it\ninto actually usable water."},{"time":492397,"text":"Like a lot of predators,\nthey walk on their toes."},{"time":496336,"text":"But there's a big fat pad\nin there that squishes out."},{"time":500000,"text":"They're like sun shoes,\nbut, you know, with sand."},{"time":505870,"text":"Hooves? They don't have\ntraditional hooves,"},{"time":510000,"text":"but they do have one, like, big nail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":511984,"text":"(Audience laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":513302,"text":"You can't really see too clear.\nThe fur's kind of grown over."},{"time":516303,"text":"But they use their tails a lot,\nespecially in rut."},{"time":520198,"text":"He will urinate and spin his tail\nto spread the urine around"},{"time":526000,"text":"and make him more attractive."},{"time":529000,"text":"I don't know why that would be,\nbut it works for them."},{"time":532120,"text":"So, what the hell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533639,"text":"(Audience laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":535000,"text":"Now, they will also defecate\nin certain areas."},{"time":539793,"text":"Generally, they poop\nwherever they want to,"},{"time":542392,"text":"but during their rut,\nthey will defecate in perimeter areas."},{"time":548930,"text":"I don't know if you've read or heard\nabout the sub-sonic sounds from elephants,"},{"time":554000,"text":"you know what I mean, like, \"Br-r-r!\""},{"time":557000,"text":"These big, big rumbling sounds.\nHe will do the same thing."},{"time":560000,"text":"You can actually see,\nright here, it will vibrate."},{"time":563911,"text":"We weigh our animals."},{"time":565833,"text":"Unfortunately,\nhe's a very aggressive animal,"},{"time":570000,"text":"so he's actually destroyed\nsome of the scales."},{"time":573000,"text":"We had these big things that I weigh\nthe bison on, for instance."},{"time":576072,"text":"I'm guessing that\nhe's at least 1,600 pounds."},{"time":579820,"text":"But I would put him closer to 2,000."},{"time":582000,"text":"He's basically a walking mulch pile."},{"time":584415,"text":"We're kind of like buds,\nbut I'm also a male as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587541,"text":"KB: He sees you as competition?\nSenior Keeper: Yeah, exactly."},{"time":590468,"text":"And it makes him very dangerous\nat this time of year."},{"time":593000,"text":"Don't even think about it.\nDon't think about it!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":599034,"text":"But now, we're going to meet. Out!"},{"time":602714,"text":"Out! Out!"},{"time":606927,"text":"No."},{"time":609000,"text":"Out!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":611442,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":634976,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636000,"text":"KB: What I didn't show you was,\nyou got that swinging thing going?"},{"time":641324,"text":"Well, and you're glad\nI didn't show you this."},{"time":644422,"text":"One of the other things\nabout the camel's beautiful design"},{"time":647200,"text":"is that its penis points backwards."},{"time":649414,"text":"That way the camel can dip\nits tail in the stream,"},{"time":653541,"text":"and just whacker\nthe entire area around him."},{"time":657000,"text":"And that's how\nhe really marks his territory."},{"time":659492,"text":"Now, what you also didn't see was that --"},{"time":662000,"text":"and you may have noticed\nin the pen beside him"},{"time":665000,"text":"and, by the way, the camel's name is Suki."},{"time":667778,"text":"In the pen beside him is Jasmine."},{"time":670000,"text":"Jasmine has been his mate for some time."},{"time":672270,"text":"But on this particular occasion,\nit was very, very clear"},{"time":675734,"text":"that as horny as Suki was,\nJasmine was having none of it."},{"time":681000,"text":"And so we started thinking."},{"time":683000,"text":"Well, if poor old Suki\nis in search of a mate,"},{"time":687000,"text":"what would Suki do to find\nthe perfect mate?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":689802,"text":"I'm going to show you another film."},{"time":691499,"text":"But before I do, I just want to mention"},{"time":693873,"text":"that this animal truly is a sort\nof the SUV of the sand,"},{"time":698000,"text":"the ship of the desert."},{"time":700450,"text":"It's so vital to the inhabitants\nof the areas"},{"time":706000,"text":"in which the camel is found,\nlargely Mongolia and Sahara,"},{"time":708746,"text":"that there are 160 words\nin Arabic to describe the camel."},{"time":714293,"text":"And if this is a creature\nthat was designed by committee,"},{"time":717000,"text":"it's certainly been\nlike no committee I've ever been on."},{"time":720000,"text":"So here's what Suki would do\nin search of a mate."},{"time":726864,"text":"Can you roll it, please?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":728048,"text":"Camel seeking camel"},{"time":729675,"text":"Lusty beast desires\nattractive and sincere mate."},{"time":732635,"text":"I'm seven feet, 2,000 lbs.,\nwith brown hair and eyes, long legs --"},{"time":735898,"text":"and I'm very well ... hung."},{"time":742483,"text":"I'm TED Camel."},{"time":744159,"text":"The perfect desert machine."},{"time":748239,"text":"I'm smartly designed."},{"time":750794,"text":"Eyelashes that keep out sand"},{"time":752459,"text":"and a third eyelash that works\nlike a windshield wiper."},{"time":757000,"text":"A distinguished nose --"},{"time":760000,"text":"with nostrils lined\nto filter out sand and dust"},{"time":764883,"text":"and a groove that catches moisture."},{"time":767762,"text":"Amazingly full lips --"},{"time":772000,"text":"that allow me to eat practically\nanything that grows."},{"time":777000,"text":"Callouses on my knees\nthat let me kneel comfortably."},{"time":783000,"text":"Leathery chest pads that beat the heat."},{"time":786000,"text":"Short fur that keeps my skin cool."},{"time":790000,"text":"Long legs that allow heat to escape."},{"time":795000,"text":"And my hump?"},{"time":798000,"text":"Ogden Nash once wrote:"},{"time":800000,"text":"\"The camel has a single hump;\nthe dromedary two,"},{"time":802263,"text":"or else the other way around.\nI'm never sure. Are you?\""},{"time":805899,"text":"Here's a hint:"},{"time":807000,"text":"Bactarian."},{"time":809000,"text":"Dromedary."},{"time":813745,"text":"My hump contains up to 80 lbs. of fat,\nbut doesn't store H2O."},{"time":818000,"text":"I'm built to last."},{"time":823492,"text":"I'm the go-to animal\nwhen the oasis is dry."},{"time":827000,"text":"I usually won't sweat\nuntil my body reaches 105 ºF,"},{"time":829405,"text":"enough to fry an egg."},{"time":832000,"text":"I'm able to lose 40%\nof my weight without dying."},{"time":837249,"text":"(Most animals would\nif they lost half that much.)"},{"time":841000,"text":"I'll drink 5 to 7 gallons\nof water a day."},{"time":847000,"text":"But go without for more than a month."},{"time":849714,"text":"I'm powerful."},{"time":851430,"text":"Able to pack up to 400 lbs. of cargo."},{"time":856000,"text":"Outrun a horse --"},{"time":859809,"text":"And cover 26 miles on a good day."},{"time":864589,"text":"Camelot."},{"time":866000,"text":"Jackie O. once said\nthat traveling by camel"},{"time":868072,"text":"made riding an elephant seem\nlike taking a jet plane."},{"time":874952,"text":"Yet my large, soft feet\nallow me to navigate sand."},{"time":880000,"text":"(Is that why the Bedouin\nclaim I can dance?)"},{"time":885000,"text":"I'm a good provider, too."},{"time":887000,"text":"Bedouins call the camel the Gift of God."},{"time":889841,"text":"No surprise."},{"time":891132,"text":"Tents and rugs are made of my hair."},{"time":893000,"text":"My dried bones are prized\nas a sort of ivory."},{"time":895167,"text":"My dung is burned as fuel.\nMy milk is used for cheese."},{"time":897763,"text":"\"Camels are like angels,\"\na Bedouin once said."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":904603,"text":"Thank you. I just want to leave you\nwith one last thought,"},{"time":908000,"text":"which is probably the most important\nthing to take away."},{"time":912722,"text":"Humans, the animal, are pretty lucky\ncreatures because, by and large,"},{"time":919000,"text":"we really don't have\nto adapt to our environment;"},{"time":923000,"text":"we adapt our environment to us."},{"time":925000,"text":"And we've seen that repeatedly\nthrough this conference,"},{"time":928000,"text":"not just this year, but in past years."},{"time":930000,"text":"But this creature that you've just seen"},{"time":933000,"text":"ultimately adapts,\nand keeps adapting and adapting."},{"time":935858,"text":"I think when you look\nat the animal kingdom,"},{"time":938000,"text":"that is one of the most remarkable things."},{"time":940024,"text":"It doesn't have an environment\nthat adapts to it;"},{"time":942934,"text":"it has to adapt to the environment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":944754,"text":"Ricky, thank you very much for having me."}]},{"cues":[{"time":946753,"text":"RW: That's terrific. Thank you."}]}]}